Followed the recipe verbatim, except the brown sugar (realized that I was out, and subbed a mixture of molasses and white sugar). I let it marinate for 24 hours. Be very gentle with the time on the grill, folks. Super high heat on the grill is fabulous for caramelization, but white meat dries pretty quickly at high temps. So get the color you want with 2 minutes (max) per side, then turn down the flame. Served with Hugh Acheson's watermelon, feta and serrano salad. Perfect.

