A fantastic and easy dish. Include some coriander/cilantro roots if possible for even better flavour. Dinner guests have raved over this dish. If they like thai-inspired cuisine you can't go wrong.

Rating: 4
This is a wonderful, easy recipe. I used basil from a jar since I could not find any fresh the day I prepared it, and then let it marinate for 2 days as opposed to just over night. I then barbecued it over a low flame until it was pretty much done, then raised the flames to high for a few minutes to crisp it. Tasted quite similar to a Larb Gai(sp?) salad. Markus